%N A394428 Decimal expansion of Product_{p prime} ((1-1/p^2) * Sum_{k>=0} 1/p^(2*k^2)).
%C A394428 The asymptotic probability that the greatest common divisor of two positive integers selected independently at random is a number whose prime factorization exponents are all squares (A197680).
%F A394428 0.926958114302935853711117828077278931039236695926607...
%o A394428 (PARI) c(m) = prodeulerrat((1-1/p^2) * sum(k=0,m,1/p^(2*k^2)));
%o A394428 {my(c1 = 0, c2 = 1, m = 1); while(c2 != c1, c1 = c2; c2 = c(m); m++); c2}
%Y A394428 Cf. A197680, A394427.
